points_to_sample means the time it will take (points = frames) to travel through the spline from the start point to the end. It can differ from the project frame count to achieve more controllable results.

nodes.title: Auto Prompt
widgets_values: A detailed digital painting of a female knight with long, flowing red hair, wearing ornate silver and gold armor with a purple cape. She has a serious expression and is holding a sword in her right hand. The background is a dark, smoky gradient. The art style is realistic with a focus on texture and detail. The knight is positioned in the center of the image, facing the viewer.

nodes.title: Auto Prompt
widgets_values: A 3D rendering of a cute, cartoon penguin standing on a solid light blue background. The penguin has a black and white body with a yellow beak and feet, and a small tuft of black hair on its head. It has a friendly expression and is looking directly at the viewer. The lighting is soft and even, casting gentle shadows on the penguin's body. The background is simple and minimalistic, with no other objects or decorations in sight. The image is high quality and has a playful, whimsical feel.

when no control_images, num_frames is the length of the start-to-end frame, which is useful for controlling the transition time. It can be different to be the project video length, which can achieve more controllable results than other flf2v methods.

control_images can control how the start-to-end frame transforms, using depth | lineart | pose etc.

use inpaint_mask with inpaint control video.

start | end frame, control images, and inpaint masks all can be generated from original video.

VACE reference image can be the same as the common ref image generated based on the video first frame. However, it can be more complicated using 1 to 3 reference images, including main subjects with a white background and/or background image, batch/concatenate them as one image grid with/without scaling them to the project/video resolution.

1. Build your reference images yourself using 1-3 images based on the need.
2. Link the chosen one (brown color) to the Setter.
a group node cannot link to set node directly. So that link the Image Input Switch JK🐉 node - image_false slot instead.

widgets_values: An young elf, gracefully dancing Barllet in a dimly lit room with a wooden staircase in the background. The lighting is soft and diffused, casting gentle shadows on the dancer's body.
If you have first and/or last frame inpainted using image generation. It's recomendded to choose ff2vid | flf2vid + inpaint control video, but might need to dislink the reference images.

If the First and/or Last frame is outpainted for VACE ffvid | flfvid Outpaint workflow, bypass the Enchance And Resize Hint Images JK🐉 node. Or change the width and height if needed to match the output resolution after outpaint.
If you have first and/or last frame outpainted using image generation. It's recomendded to choose ff2vid | flf2vid + outpaint control video.

(default) bypass Torch Compile Mode Wan Video if you're using fp8 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx

If you choose VACE fp32/bf16/fp16 model, then you can change weight_dtype to default and link Torch Compile Mode Wan Video to the workflow to speed up about 15%~25%.

For single reference image only:
1. The reference image should be as close as possible to the first frame of the control video. 
2. Bypass crop by mask and resize node in the Load Reference Group.
3. Enable this group and link to the WanVideo VACE Encode node's ref_image slot to replace the first 3 frames of control video with the reference image.
